</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Nicholas Gilman (17311783) of Exeter was receiver general (treasurer) of New Hampshire from 1775 to 1782. He also commanded a militia regiment 177577 and served on the New Hampshire committee of safety and executive council, 177783.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Schuyler is referring to Monday 13 May and Friday 17 May.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>The following day was Wednesday.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>A transcript of Schuylers letter to Elias Dayton of 14 May 1776 directing him to arrest Sir John Johnson and to evacuate the Highlanders from the Mohawk Valley is in the Jared Sparks Papers at Harvard University. See also Schuyler to John Johnston, 14 May 1776, MH: Sparks Papers.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0297-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0296" class="document">GW to Schuyler, this date</a>.</p>

</div>
